    <div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='25478#1434138575'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2015-06-12T19:49:35+00:00">Jun 12, 2015 07:49 PM UTC</time> by <b>echism</b><a class="anchor" name="1434138575">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Closing as advised, thanks1</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='25478#1433973639'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2015-06-10T22:00:39+00:00">Jun 10, 2015 10:00 PM UTC</time><a class="anchor" name="1433973639">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Yes. Thanks for fixing!

by /DC=com/DC=DigiCert-Grid/O=Open Science Grid/OU=People/CN=Mats Rynge 45</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='25478#1433962177'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2015-06-10T18:49:37+00:00">Jun 10, 2015 06:49 PM UTC</time> by <b>echism</b><a class="anchor" name="1433962177">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Hey Mats,

May I close this?

Thanks</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='25478#1433875944'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2015-06-09T18:52:24+00:00">Jun 9, 2015 06:52 PM UTC</time> by <b>Thomas Lee</b><a class="anchor" name="1433875944">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>The DNS resolver timeout is back to its 5-second default, on xd-login and everywhere else.  I hope this doesn&#39;t cause any problems, but it should mean no further premature-timeout issues such as this one.</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='25478#1432161914'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2015-05-20T22:45:14+00:00">May 20, 2015 10:45 PM UTC</time><a class="anchor" name="1432161914">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>ITB/production cycle is fine. Thanks!

by /DC=com/DC=DigiCert-Grid/O=Open Science Grid/OU=People/CN=Mats Rynge 45</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='25478#1432154647'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2015-05-20T20:44:07+00:00">May 20, 2015 08:44 PM UTC</time> by <b>Thomas Lee</b><a class="anchor" name="1432154647">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Well currently in /etc/resolv.conf, I see

nameserver 127.0.0.1
options timeout&#58;1

because, like all hosts here, it&#39;s running dnsmasq as a local caching/forwarding nameserver.  Why it would take longer than 1 second for the local dnsmasq to respond I don&#39;t know, unless the machine is extraordinarily loaded down.  But I think the 1-second timeout was historical, hearkening back to a time when we did things differently and had a list of nameservers there, wanting to move quickly on to the next one when the first one didn&#39;t work rather than sit around for several seconds (5 seconds is the default), causing some other software to timeout and emit an error when there was nothing really wrong.

I don&#39;t want to make a special exception for xd-login; I try to avoid those whenever possible (the more exceptions, the less maintainability), but with all machines using a local dnsmasq I think removing that timeout (reverting to the 5-second default) is probably the best option.  I will do that globally, though it will have to wait for the usual itb/production cycle.  Do you need this changed faster?</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='25478#1432153155'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2015-05-20T20:19:15+00:00">May 20, 2015 08:19 PM UTC</time> by <b>Kyle Gross</b><a class="anchor" name="1432153155">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>I am sending this to Tom Lee.

Tom, can you please investigate as needed?

-Kyle</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='25478#1432051677'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2015-05-19T16:07:57+00:00">May 19, 2015 04:07 PM UTC</time> by <b>Vince Neal</b><a class="anchor" name="1432051677">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>GOC,

We have had this problem before on xd-login, but it is now back again. A user reports&#58;

I have noticed an apparent naming hiccup on xd-login and when ssh’g to blacklight.psc.xsede.org .
I often get an error the first time I try it&#58;
ssh&#58; Could not resolve hostname blacklight.psc.xsede.org&#58; Temporary failure in name resolution
When I try a 2nd time immediately, it always works.

I think last time we increased the DNS lookup timeout, but maybe it got changed back again by puppet?

--
Mats Rynge
